programme.desc: Wolverhampton Wanderers (4-4-14) take on Arsenal (12-8-2) in a Premier League contest. The Gunners are targeting a fourth consecutive season sweep of Wolves, having won seven straight meetings after securing a 2-0 victory on Aug. 17, 2024.

programme.title: NBA Basketball
programme.sub-title: Indiana Pacers at San Antonio Spurs
programme.desc: Victor Wembanyama and the Spurs play the Pacers in the NBA Paris Games. Hall of Famer Tony Parker had his No. 9 jersey retired by the French Federation of Basketball in July 2024. Parker played for San Antonio from 2001-2018, winning four NBA titles.

programme.title: NBA Countdown
programme.desc: Bold opinions, discussion and debate centered on the top storylines from around the league. Mike Greenberg hosts this pregame show with analysts Stephen A. Smith and Michael Wilbon.

programme.title: NBA Basketball
programme.desc: The Timberwolves tip off against the Nuggets. Minnesota has won three straight meetings - Game 6 and 7 of its 2024 Western Conference semifinal with Denver, and a 119-116 decision Nov. 1, 2024. Denver has won six consecutive road games.

programme.title: NBA Basketball
programme.desc: The Celtics and Mavericks do battle for the first time since the 2024 NBA Finals. Boston secured its 18th championship, and first since 2008, by knocking off Dallas in five games. Cs star Jaylen Brown averaged 20.8 points and was named Finals MVP.

programme.title: NBA Countdown
programme.desc: Bold opinions, discussion and debate centered on the top storylines from around the league. Mike Greenberg hosts this pregame show with analysts Stephen A. Smith and Michael Wilbon.

programme.title: NBA Basketball
programme.sub-title: Los Angeles Lakers at Golden State Warriors
programme.desc: The stars shine on San Francisco Bay as LeBron James and the Lakers visit the Warriors. James scored 31 points in a 115-113 Los Angeles victory over Golden State on Christmas Day 2024. Stephen Curry (GS) tallied a game-high 38 in that contest.

programme.title: College Basketball
programme.desc: The Bulldogs (15-4, 5-1) visit the Mocs (12-7, 4-2) in a clash of Southern Conference contenders. Samfords 28-game home win streak was stopped by East Tennessee State 65-60 on Jan. 18. Bash Wieland paces Chattanooga with 13.4 points per game.

programme.title: College Basketball
programme.desc: The Ohio Valley Conference-leading Eagles visit the Panthers. Morehead State has won four in a row, and nine of its past 10 overall. Morehead State won both meetings in 2023-24 to stretch its win streak over Eastern Illinois to seven games.

programme.title: College Basketball
programme.desc: The Lancers host the Wolverines in Western Athletic Conference play. Utah Valley has won eight straight, and six of seven versus California Baptist after a Jan. 11 decision. The Lancers lone win in that stretch came in last years WAC Tournament.

programme.title: Womens College Basketball
programme.desc: SEC heavy-hitters collide as the No. 7 Longhorns (18-2, 4-1) host the No. 17 Lady Volunteers (15-3, 3-3). This is the first meeting between the programs in the Lone Star State since 2018. Texas is coming off an 89-51 walloping of No. 8 Maryland.

programme.title: College Basketball
programme.desc: PJ Haggerty and the No. 24 Tigers (14-4, 4-1 American) host the Shockers (11-7, 1-4). Haggerty, a sophomore guard, is among the nations leading scorers at 22.1 points per outing. Wichita State snapped an eight-game slide against Memphis last season.

programme.title: 30 for 30
programme.desc: Having worn out his welcome in the NBA, Paul Westhead heads to Loyola Marymount University to perfect his run-and-gun offensive system with players Hank Gathers and Bo Kimble.

programme.title: Unsportsmanlike with Evan, Canty and Michelle
programme.desc: Start the day off right with Chris Canty, Evan Cohen and Michelle Smallmon providing an energizing and informative way to take on the day. Sports, life and laughter are what its all about.

programme.title: Playoff Semifinal at the Capital One Orange Bowl
programme.desc: The No. 6 Nittany Lions and No. 7 Fighting Irish meet in a CFP semifinal at the Orange Bowl. Drew Allar threw for three TDs, two to Tyler Warren, as Penn State ousted Boise State in the Fiesta Bowl. Notre Dame got past Georgia in the Sugar Bowl.

programme.title: Playoff Semifinal at the Goodyear Cotton Bowl Classic
programme.desc: The No. 8 Buckeyes burst into their CFP semifinal against the No. 5 Longhorns in the Cotton Bowl. Ohio State routed No. 1 Oregon 41-21 in the quarters. Texas coughed up a 16-point lead before surviving No. 4 Arizona State 39-31 in double overtime.

programme.title: CFP National Championship
programme.desc: The No. 7 Fighting Irish (14-1) battle the No. 8 Buckeyes (13-2) in the College Football Playoff final from Atlanta. Notre Dame seeks a 12th championship but the first for the storied school since 1988, while Ohio State aims for its ninth title.

programme.title: College Basketball
programme.desc: Ohio (10-8, 4-2 MAC) tries to shake a two-game slide when it hosts Kent State (12-6, 3-3). Last season, the Bobcats swept both matches from the Golden Flashes for the first time since 2012-13. Ohios Shereef Mitchell averaged 12 points in those wins.

programme.title: College Basketball
programme.desc: The Rams look to exact some revenge on the Bonnies in Atlantic 10 action. St. Bonaventure won its fourth straight clash against VCU on New Years Eve 2024, when Melvin Council Jr.s layup with three seconds remaining clinched a 77-75 victory.

programme.title: College Basketball
programme.desc: The Flyers (13-6, 3-3 A-10) welcome the Hawks (12-7, 3-3) to the Buckeye State. Dayton has won two straight entering this matchup, with senior guard Enoch Cheeks scoring 49 points. Saint Josephs looks to end a four-game slide against Dayton.

programme.title: College Basketball

programme.title: Womens College Basketball

programme.desc: The Golden Bears (10-9, 3-5 ACC) take on the Hurricanes (4-15, 0-8) for the first time. California has won two in a row after rolling past Florida State 77-68 without leading scorer Andrej Stojaković, who was sidelined with an illness, on Jan. 22.
